<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_998c665b-59d2-422d-ab52-2de2821f9323" outputclass="ncc-clause"><sptc>B1D3</sptc><title id="_861c2098-f442-4253-a6a5-ce9b920f403e">General requirements</title><archive-num>2019: B1.4</archive-num><clause-variation href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4187_1.4.0.xml" variation="VIC" variation-type="REPLACE">VIC REPLACE Clause</clause-variation><clause-variation href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4186_1.7.0.xml" variation="TAS" variation-type="REPLACE">TAS REPLACE Clause</clause-variation><clause-variation href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4184_0.10.0.xml" variation="NSW" variation-type="REPLACE">NSW REPLACE Clause</clause-variation><subclause id="_0604416e-e889-419b-b891-a751c80e5821" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_2dc29612-2941-4d87-8304-dd1fe474db8c">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A cold water service must be in accordance with AS/NZS 3500.1.</p></subclause><subclause id="_0bce9f03-d130-4bad-bd1c-80eae116104d" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_8cb79f6b-4b47-4378-8ac4-1d9d291dccd2">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Notwithstanding (1), plastic pipes and fittings must not be used above-ground in combined sprinkler and hydrant systems.</p></subclause><subclause id="_f93aad9b-04cc-4c9e-87dc-06ef58e2a937" outputclass="state-variation-insert" variation="QLD" variation-type="INSERT"><title id="_6549ef75-46eb-4555-b508-aa44b3fe4d38">QLD INSERT SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Notwithstanding (1), Appendix I of AS/NZS 3500.1 is adopted as an Informative appendix.</p></subclause><subclause id="_692d1f27-04d7-4d63-8394-fed683ecfbe3" outputclass="state-variation-insert" variation="QLD" variation-type="INSERT"><title id="_a8e68398-4db1-4029-94ee-fc0324da1234">QLD INSERT SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>For clause 2.5.3(c) of AS/NZS 3500.1, the minimum pressure rating for plastic pipes used in a cold water service is PN 12.</p></subclause></clause>